<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-04-07T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-04-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="194" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">858.116 M 82/29: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-07T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 7,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>20. Department’s No. 17, April 2, 5 p.m. Your No. 40 April 4, 4 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Telegraph Swedish Government’s reasons for expelling Mormons. Request no
                            drastic action be taken until matter can be fully investigated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>